************************************************* READ ME PLEASE ! ************************************************
This read me is about how to install our shell.

1 - Prerequisites :
    Two libraries need to be installed before installing our shell : ncurses and libreadline.
    Just type the following commands on the terminal in order to install the two libraries :

		sudo apt-get install libreadline-dev
   	        sudo apt-get install libncurses5-dev libncursesw5-dev

2 - Installation :
    - Go to the directory location of the downloaded debian package.
    - open the terminal from there and type the following commands :
                sudo dpkg -i [name_of_the_package].deb
		sudo apt-get install -f

3 - Launch :
    Now The shell is installed. In order to launch it, just go to the application search bar and type the name of the program.

